'''Mateo Chávez García''' (born 12 May 2004) is a Mexican professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] for {{Dutch football updater|AZAlkmaar}} club [[AZ Alkmaar]] and the [[Mexico national football team|Mexico national team]].

==Club career==
===Guadalajara===
====Tapatío====
Chávez made his professional debut with [[C.D. Tapatío|Tapatío]] on 29 September 2022, coming on as a 60th-minute substitute against  [[Venados F.C.|Venados]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/09/30/mexico/liga-de-ascenso/tapatio/monarcas-merida/3799779/ |title=Tapatío vs. Venados 1 - 0|website=Soccerway|date=29 September 2022|access-date=22 September 2024}}</ref>

====First team====
Chávez made his first team, and [[Liga MX]] debut on 13 January 2024, in a 1–1 draw against [[Santos Laguna]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2024/01/14/mexico/primera-division/club-guadalajara/club-santos-laguna/4285256/ |title=Guadalajara 1–1 Santos Laguna (13 Jan. 2024) Summary|website=Soccerway|date=14 January 2024|access-date=25 February 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.tudn.com/futbol/liga-mx/chivas-mateo-chavez-hijo-paulo-cesar-tilon-chavez-debuta-especial-numero|title=
Mateo Chávez, hijo de 'Tilón' Chávez, debuta en Chivas con especial número |publisher=TUDN|date=13 January 2024|access-date=22 September 2024}}</ref> On 7 February 2024, Chávez made his [[CONCACAF Champions Cup]] debut in a 3–1 win against [[Forge FC|Forge]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chivasdecorazon.com.mx/es/noticias/37344/Chivas-vence-al-Forge-FC-en-Canad |title=
Chivas vence al Forge FC en Canadá |publisher=Club Deportivo Guadalajara|date=7 February 2024}}</ref>

=== AZ ===
On 15 May 2025, Chávez signed for Dutch club [[AZ Alkmaar]] on a four-year agreement with a transfer fee of €2 million for 75% of Chavez's rights while Guadalajara retains the other 25%.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Chávez Joins AZ Alkmaar as Chivas Secure Lucrative Sell-On Clause |url=https://dailysports.net/news/chavez-joins-az-alkmaar-as-chivas-secure-lucrative-sellon-clause/ |access-date=14 May 2025 |website=dailysports.net |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Mateo Chavez Embarks on European Journey to Join AZ Alkmaar |url=https://www.footboom1.com/en/news/football/2560500-mateo-chavez-embarks-on-european-journey-to-join-az-alkmaar |access-date=14 May 2025 |website=www.footboom1.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=16 May 2025 |title=Chivas gem Mateo Chávez joins AZ Alkmaar on deal until 2029 {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/chivas-gem-mateo-chavez-joins-az-alkmaar-on-deal-until-2029/bltf4a5dfa4ef462f7e |access-date=14 December 2025 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> On 10 August, he made his [[Eredivisie]] debut, providing an assist, in a 4–1 victory against [[FC Groningen|Groningen]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=RAÍZ |date=10 August 2025 |title=¡Talento mexicano! Mateo Chávez debuta en Eredivisie con asistencia en Az Alkmaar vs Groningen |url=https://www.marca.com/mx/futbol/mexicanos-mundo/2025/08/10/6898b79f268e3e0c498b4582.html |access-date=14 December 2025 |website=Marca México |language=es-MX}}</ref>

==International career==
In March 2024, [[Mexico national under-23 football team|Mexico under-23 team]] coach [[Ricardo Cadena]] included Chávez in the roster for friendlies against [[Argentina national under-23 football team|Argentina]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hernandez |first=Rafael |date=16 March 2024 |title=Mexico announce call up list for U-23 friendlies against Argentina |url=https://www.fmfstateofmind.com/2024/3/16/24100382/mexico-national-team-announce-call-up-list-for-u-23-friendlies-against-argentina |access-date=14 December 2025 |website=FMF State Of Mind |language=en-US}}</ref>

In June 2025, Chávez was included in [[Javier Aguirre]]'s roster for the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup|Gold Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 June 2025 |title=México presenta lista final para la Copa Oro 2025 |url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/copa-oro/nota/_/id/15272774/seleccion-mexicana-convocatoria-final-copa-oro-2025-lista |access-date=14 December 2025 |website=ESPNdeportes.com |language=es}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Chávez is the son of former professional footballer [[Paulo Chávez]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chivasdecorazon.com.mx/en/noticias/37224/La-asombrosa-coincidencia-de-Mateo-Chvez-y-Armando-Gonzlez |title=The amazing coincidence of Mateo Chávez and Armando González|publisher=Club Deportivo Guadalajara|date=16 January 2024|access-date=22 September 2024}}</ref>

